{"parse":{"title":"Synergy School Radio","pageid":25849463,"revid":848365245,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Synergy School Radio</caption><tbody><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.5em;\">Industry</th><td class=\"category\" style=\"line-height:1.35em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Broadcasting\" title=\"Broadcasting\">Broadcasting</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Education\" title=\"Education\">Education</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.5em;\">Founded</th><td style=\"line-height:1.35em;\">\n(2001) developed as part of <a href=\"/wiki/Clyde_Broadcast\" title=\"Clyde Broadcast\">Clyde Broadcast</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.5em;\">Headquarters</th><td class=\"label\" style=\"line-height:1.35em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Clydebank\" title=\"Clydebank\">Clydebank</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Scotland\" title=\"Scotland\">Scotland</a>. Neighbouring <a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow\" title=\"Glasgow\">Glasgow</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.5em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Area served</div></th><td style=\"line-height:1.35em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/UK\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"UK\">UK</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.5em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Key people</div></th><td class=\"agent\" style=\"line-height:1.35em;\">\n<p><b>Paul McGarry</b><br /><small>(Marketing)</small> \n<b>Brian Rowan</b><br /><small>(Director)</small>\n<b>Darren Dixie</b><br /><small>(Media Projects Consultant)</small> \n</p>\n<b>Nigel Vernon Dier</b><br /><small>(Trainer)</small></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.5em;\">Website</th><td style=\"line-height:1.35em;\">\n<span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.synergyschoolradio.com\">www<wbr />.synergyschoolradio<wbr />.com</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Synergy School Radio</b> is a digital integrated radio studio built and designed by <a href=\"/wiki/Clyde_Broadcast\" title=\"Clyde Broadcast\">Clyde Broadcast</a>. Synergy is the UK's leading digital radio studio currently used in education in the UK.\nRadio is a growing tool within education and is regularly cited for good practice and innovation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nSchool Radio projects have often received significant support from government and education consultants a like advocating the use of School Radio projects as part of good practice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Synergy were behind the Determined to Broadcast bus. The bus received both support and sponsorship from Synergy but it was also Synergy radio studios that made up the core of the technology being used. The Synergy School Radio project received high-profile support from  <a href=\"/wiki/Radio_Clyde\" title=\"Radio Clyde\">Radio Clyde</a>'s <a href=\"/wiki/Ross_King_(presenter)\" title=\"Ross King (presenter)\">Ross King (presenter)</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Gina_McKie&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Gina McKie (page does not exist)\">Gina McKie</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/XFM\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"XFM\">XFM</a> Scotland's <a href=\"/wiki/Heather_Suttie\" title=\"Heather Suttie\">Heather Suttie</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/GMTV\" title=\"GMTV\">GMTV</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Radio_presenter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Radio presenter\">presenter</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Jenni_Falconer\" title=\"Jenni Falconer\">Jenni Falconer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Synergy School Radio are associated sponsors of the Sony Award category \"Best School Radio station\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Education_sites_using_Synergy\">Education sites using Synergy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Synergy_School_Radio&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Education sites using Synergy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Ashmole_School\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ashmole School\">Ashmole School</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Saltash.net\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Saltash.net\">saltash.net</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Derby\" title=\"University of Derby\">University of Derby</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Blackpool_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Blackpool College\">Blackpool College</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow_Caledonian_University\" title=\"Glasgow Caledonian University\">Glasgow Caledonian University</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/St._Thomas_Aquinas_Secondary_School,_Jordanhill\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"St. Thomas Aquinas Secondary School, Jordanhill\">St. Thomas Aquinas Secondary School, Jordanhill</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Gordon_University\" title=\"Robert Gordon University\">Robert Gordon University</a></li>\n<li>Pulse FM<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Archbishop_Ilsley_Catholic_Technology_College_and_Sixth_Form_Centre\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archbishop Ilsley Catholic Technology College and Sixth Form Centre\">Archbishop Ilsley Catholic Technology College and Sixth Form Centre</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Cardinal_Wiseman_Catholic_Technology_College\" title=\"Cardinal Wiseman Catholic Tec